Node.Notes: Either "a person without knowledge"/"desire without knowledge" is not good.
Something like a person who is hasty with his feet/being in a rush/hurry misses his way/goal.
Some question this form; but perhaps taking it with the verb as "is separated from his friend" makes sense of the text.
"Beg the face" may be seeking favor/praise/flatter.
""To pusue with words" probably something like "he tries to talk to them.""
Uncertain. "They are not to him" maybe in sense of "he pursues words which are nothing" (i.e., his efforts to talk with his friends does not help."
Either who neglects the ways of the Lord or has no concern for own conduct/life.
Probably the destruction he will bring on himself if he is not disciplined.
Scoffers and the simple appear to be two different groups; the simple learn by seeing the scoffers punished.
Uncertain. Perhaps irony? Or reorder to yield "Stop straying from words of knowledge so as to listen to instruction." Or "if you stop ... it is to stray ..."
